    "# Variables & Data Types\n",
    "## From Algebraic Variables to Python Memory\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/VictorMuv/math-with-python/blob/main/1_python_foundations/1_variables_datatypes.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Traditional Algebra\n",
    "In equations like `3x + 2 = 11`, `x` is a placeholder for an unknown value.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Python Implementation\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# PEP 8 compliant variable naming\n",
    "coefficient = 3  # int type\n",
    "constant = 2     # int type\n",
    "result = 11.0    # float type (for division later)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Solving equation: 3x + 2 = 11\n",
    "x = (result - constant) / coefficient\n",
    "print(f\"The solution is x = {x:.2f}\")  # Formatted to 2 decimal places\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Memory Visualization\n",
    "```\n",
    "Memory Map:\n",
    "coefficient → [3] (int)\n",
    "constant    → [2] (int)\n",
    "x           → [3.0] (float)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Python is Better\n",
    "- Exact decimal handling (vs. manual fraction conversion)\n",
    "- Instant verification: `print(3*3.0 + 2 == 11)` → `True`\n",
    "- Reusable for any linear equation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Challenge\n",
    "Solve `5y - 3 = 22`:\n",
    "1. Create variables for each component\n",
    "2. Compute the solution\n",
    "3. Verify by plugging back in\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# Student's workspace\n",
    "a = ?\n",
    "b = ?\n",
    "c = ?\n",
    "y = ?  # Your solution here\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Instructor's Solution (collapse this cell in the actual notebook)\n",
    "a = 5\n",
    "b = -3  # Note the sign change!\n",
    "c = 22\n",
    "y = (c - b) / a\n",
    "print(f\"y = {y}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Verification: {5*y - 3 == 22}\")"
   ]
